{
  "doc_id": "16681",
  "text": "Surotomycin is a novel, oral lipopeptide antibiotic that has demonstrated bactericidal effects in vitro against C. difficile [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . An initial, double-blinded Phase 2 RCT (n = 209) showed clinical cure rates of surotomycin 125 mg twice daily (92.4%), surotomycin 250 mg twice daily (86.6%), and vancomycin 125 mg four times daily (89.4%) for 10 days. The recurrences were also lower for surotomycin (17.2% for 250 mg; 27.9% for 125 mg) compared to vancomycin (35.6%) [CITATION_3] . This trial was followed by two parallel, double-blinded Phase 3 RCTs, one of which (n = 577) demonstrated that the clinical cure rate of surotomycin 250 mg twice daily (83.4%) was noninferior to vancomycin 125 mg four times daily (82.1%) at Day 10 [CITATION_4] . In contrast, the parallel Phase 3 study (n = 570) failed to show noninferiority at the same doses [CITATION_5] . In addition, neither study met the criteria for superiority of surotomycin over vancomycin, although recurrence rates were found to be lower for surotomycin compared to vancomycin (14.0% vs. 50.4%; 95% CI, −54.1 to −15.1) [CITATION_6] . In all three studies, adverse events were similar among treated groups. Further studies are needed to characterize the role of surotomycin.",
